  "description": "Immature plumage: blue on crown of head, long, sinuous reddish neck, reddish color continued into the blue of the wings, white stripe down center of throat and white breast, white underparts, and white rump, yellow green legs and long, dagger-like yellow bill. \u00a0Smaller than Great Blue Heron. \u00a0Non-vocal. \u00a0Wading and hunting for prey in shallow waters of Cottonwood Marsh at Walden Ponds in Boulder County, CO. \u00a0Standing, sometimes on one leg and preening on the small islands in the pond.",
